Definition: the Roman Catholic doctrine that the whole substance of the bread and the wine changes into the substance of the body and blood of Christ when consecrated in the Eucharist
Synonyms: verb, change, transubstantiate, theological_doctrine, the, Roman, Catholic, doctrine, that, whole, substance, of, bread, and, wine, changes, into, body, blood, Christ, when, consecrated, in, Eucharist
Category: noun.cognition
